&lt;h1 id="part-1">PART 1.&lt;/h1>
&lt;h2 id="introduction">&lt;strong>Introduction&lt;/strong>&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Cooking varies in complexity. Some recipes are straightforward, while others demand precision, technique, and skill.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The challenge in this project was to develop a machine learning (ML) model that classifies recipes into four difficulty levels—&lt;strong>Easy, Medium, Hard, and Very Hard&lt;/strong>—using &lt;strong>Natural Language Processing (NLP)&lt;/strong> and &lt;strong>Machine Learning (ML)&lt;/strong>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>AI-Powered Recipe Difficulty Classification</title><link>https://drnsmith.github.io/projects/project1/</link><pubDate>Sat, 09 Apr 2022 10:58:08 -0400</pubDate><guid>https://drnsmith.github.io/projects/project1/</guid><description>&lt;h2>Read the Paper:&lt;/h2>
